This code whacked into git by Michael Meeks <michael.meeks@novell.com>
Please flame me there ...

To build me:

svn co http://svn.kulitorum.com/RepSnapper

then copy this source over RepSnapper/Src
And ln -s ../Libraries .

Why do I do that ? - well, almost none of the (800Mb)
of Libraries/ are required on Linux:

du -m Libraries | sort -n | tail:

48      Libraries/Boost1.40/doc/html/boost
51      Libraries/Boost1.40/doc/html/boost_asio
72      Libraries/Boost1.40/libs/math
77      Libraries/Boost1.40/lib
127     Libraries/Boost1.40/doc/html
130     Libraries/Boost1.40/doc
148     Libraries/Boost1.40/boost
322     Libraries/Boost1.40/libs
712     Libraries/Boost1.40
805     Libraries
